STATE of North Carolina
v.
William Britt REEVES. No. 350A95-4. Supreme Court of North Carolina. August 18, 2005. William Britt Reeves, Pro Se. William Hart, Special Deputy Attorney General, Thomas J. Keith, District Attorney, for State.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 1st day of July 2005 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Forsyth County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 18th day of August 2005."
